==Continuity==
===Differences from the film===
The novelization was based on the screenplay of [[Star Wars: Episode IV A New Hope|''Star Wars'': Episode IV ''A New Hope'']], and it has several minor differences from the final film. Some differences include:
*The novel begins with the words "Another galaxy, another time," rather than "A long time ago in a galaxy far, far away...."
*During the battle aboard the [[Tantive IV/Legends|''Tantive IV'']], the stormtroopers drop through the ceiling, rather than charging through a door.
*Before [[Leia Organa Solo/Legends|Leia Organa]] is captured, she kills two stormtroopers, instead of only one.
*Before [[Grand Moff/Legends|Grand Moff]] [[Wilhuff Tarkin/Legends|Tarkin]] and [[Anakin Skywalker/Legends|Darth Vader]] enter the conference room scene, there are eight Imperial Senators and officers around the table. In the film, there are only seven officers. During the scene, Vader uses [[The Force/Legends|the Force]] to summon a cup from the table to his hand.
*[[Conan Antonio Motti/Legends|Conan Antonio Motti]] is absent from the conference, instead the argument is between [[Cassio Tagge/Legends|Cassio Tagge]] and [[Hurst Romodi/Legends|Hurst Romodi]]. Also, it is Tagge who mocks Vader's use of [[The Force/Legends|the Force]] and is Force-choked by him.
*Skywalker's [[X-34 landspeeder/Legends|X-34 landspeeder]] has an enclosed cockpit unlike the open cockpit seen in the film.
*Skywalker's [[Lightsaber/Legends|lightsaber]] is described as having a jeweled hilt.
*In the novel, Tarkin is present during Organa's torture. In the film, Organa does not encounter Tarkin until she is taken to the [[Death Star/Legends|Death Star's]] [[Overbridge (Death Star I)/Legends|Overbridge]].
*[[Chewbacca/Legends|Chewbacca]] is described as having bright, yellow eyes.
*In the [[Cantina/Legends|cantina]], Skywalker is hassled by a trio of individuals. [[Obi-Wan Kenobi/Legends|Kenobi]] cuts a smaller alien in half and cuts off the arm of another. [[Ponda Baba/Legends|Ponda Baba]] is described as having multiple eyes.
*[[Jabba Desilijic Tiure/Legends|Jabba]] is described as a fat biped with an ugly, shaggy skull and jowls. His scars are said to be a sign of his ferocious reputation in combat.
*After the [[Destruction of Alderaan/Legends|destruction of Alderaan]], Vader reports that [[Alderaan/Legends|Alderaan]] had possessed defensive systems "as strong as that of the [[Galactic Empire/Legends|Empire]]." In the novel, Obi-Wan does not feel Alderaan's destruction through the Force.
*Stormtrooper [[TK-421/Legends|TK-421]] is identified as THX-1138.
*The [[Shann Childsen/Legends|officer]] commanding the detention block is killed activating an alarm rather than drawing a blaster. When the gang dives into the garbage chute, [[Han Solo/Legends|Han Solo]] dives in before Skywalker. The garbage chamber's number is 366-17891 instead of 3263827.
*During the [[Battle of Yavin/Legends|Battle of Yavin]], Skywalker, [[Biggs Darklighter/Legends|Biggs Darklighter]], [[Wedge Antilles/Legends|Wedge Antilles]], [[Garven Dreis/Legends|Garven Dreis]], [[Jek Tono Porkins/Legends|Porkins]], and [[John D. Branon/Legends|John D. Branon]] are in [[Blue Squadron (Rebel Alliance)/Legends|Blue Squadron]] and [[Jon Vander/Legends|Jon Vander]], [[Tiree/Legends|Tiree]], and [[Davish Krail/Legends|Davish Krail]] are in Red Squadron, but in the film, Skywalker, Darklighter, Antilles, Dreis, Porkins, and Branon are in [[Red Squadron (Rebel Alliance)/Legends|Red Squadron]] and Vander, Tiree, and Krail are in [[Gold Squadron (Rebel Alliance)/Legends|Gold Squadron]]. Skywalker also makes two attack runs through the Death Star trench. When Skywalker learns that Darklighter had been killed, his eyes begin to water and he reflects, "'We're a couple of shooting stars, Biggs' he whispered huskily, 'and we'll never be stopped.'"
*At the novel's end, Organa gives Chewbacca a medal.

===Differences from later works===
*The book's prologue quotes from the [[Journal of the Whills/Legends|Journal of the Whills]], and it says that Emperor [[Palpatine/Legends|Palpatine]] was merely a figurehead controlled by the Imperial bureaucracy.
*When Darth Vader is introduced, there's a reference to "all the Dark Lords" and Vader being more feared than the others, but the Prequel Trilogy established that Vader and his master, Darth Sidious, are the only [[Dark Lord of the Sith/Legends|Dark Lords of the Sith]] who are alive during the events of A New Hope.
*[[Obi-Wan Kenobi/Legends|Obi-Wan Kenobi]] mentions "the later corrupt Emperors", contradicting Palpatine being the one and only [[Galactic Emperor/Legends|Galactic Emperor]]. 
*Some words are spelled differently; "[[Wookiee/Legends|Wookiee]]" is spelled as "Wookie", and "[[Hutt/Legends|Hutt]]" is spelled as "Hut".

